# [[that]] (demonstrative, near the speaker)
#: [[私]]が[[読む|読みたい]][[本]][[は]]、'''その'''[[本]][[です]]。
#:: わたしがよみたいほんは、'''その'''ほんです。
#:: ''Watashi ga yomitai hon wa, '''sono''' [[hon]] desu.''
#::: What I want to read is '''that''' [[book]].

====See also====
{{Japanese demonstratives}}

====Usage notes====
* その is also used to refer to things and experiences that the listener knows about. Compare the two following sentences,
*: '''その'''本はやすいですか？
*:: Is that book (I'm pointing to/near you/of yours) cheap?
*:: Is that book which you (have/saw/were talking about) cheap?
*: '''あの'''本はやすいですか？
*:: Is that book (over there) cheap?
*The hiragana spelling ([[その]]) is preferred to the kanji spelling ([[其の]]), which is rarely used.

